															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/drmagnus" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(318209); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=318209&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610164185" alt="DrMagnus" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=318209)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/drmagnus" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(318209); return false;" >DrMagnus</a></span> <span class="odate time_1525899629 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">09 May 2018 21:00</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-3795380">
									

<p>So, firstly thank you to those who went through this with me, and encouraged me to post this.</p>
<p>This is half joke about how over the top 076-2 is, half love letter to fencing and my style in particular.</p>
<p>I see an absurd amount of hilariously bad melee combat on the wiki, and I figured a tale which had a bit of <strong>real</strong> swordsmanship in it would make me happy.</p>
<p>This may not appeal to everyone, as it'll come off a bit dry, but to those who appreciate Fiore dei Liberi, it'll cause some grins.</p>
<p>Enjoy, and keep your guard up!</p>
<p>EDIT: See how many bad sword memes you can spot in the article. If you can find them all, gold star for you &lt;3</p>

							</div>

								
