				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/lordblaze" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(3951547); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=3951547&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610164185" alt="LordBlaze" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=3951547)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/lordblaze" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(3951547); return false;" >LordBlaze</a></span> <span class="odate time_1525965859 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">10 May 2018 15:24</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-3796224">
									

<p>Swordsmanship and dueling has always fascinated me since I watched Count Dooku fight in Star Wars as a little kid. When I learned that people could do that kind of elegance and flow in real life it always made me wonder how. Seeing Able who is <em>Supposed</em> to be the ultimate killer defeated by a normal man who just happened to have years of experience and practice with a blade is insanely awesome.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>Able's voice flustered for a moment, &quot;Y-yeah, of course I have. I've been fighting with swords since the time of creation!&quot;</p>
</blockquote>
<p>This part really made me chuckle. Seeing the master killer stuttering at a simple question is just funny. The way Able is so overconfident and cocky compared to De Luca's collected nature also shines out to me. One of the first tales that I could really paint a movie into my head on how it really looked.</p>
<p>Astounding +infinity if I could</p>

							</div>

										<div class="signature">
					<hr class="signature-separator"/>
					

<p>The Holy Warrior walked. It had been a long time since he'd walked this far, but he was used to walking nonetheless.</p>

