														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-3796229">
									

<p>Interesting example! Christopher Lee in fact, was an expert real-life fencer, and designed Count Dooku's movements to mirror more realistic ones (and ones which he could accomplish at his age).</p>
<p>As for how people get this way: practice practice practice. I've been longsword fencing for going on sixteen years now, and I'm still practicing my basic strikes, a few hundred times each a day. Go through all eight, go through the advanced strikes, practice kata. Repeat. You practice until it's unconscious. Until those off-line steps are just the natural conclusion to their motion.</p>
<p>That kind of fencing is stylized, but Christopher Lee is an extraordinary human being. If anyone could <strong>be</strong> De Luca, it's him in his 30's.</p>

							</div>

								
