			<div class="content" id="post-content-3796383">
									

<p><span style="text-decoration: line-through;">0/10, De Luca did not unscrew his pommel and end 076-2 rightly.</span></p>
<p>In all seriousness, I'm neutral voting because I really dislike this interpretation of 076-2. I love you incorporating your knowledge into the story, but part of me actually wants to read 076-2 dueling like he actually knows what he's doing and giving De Luca or his equivalent a run for their money. Like, there's absolutely nothing wrong with the story, it's just that I don't care for the &quot;lol 076-2 is actually a hammy, incompetent fool&quot; version of the site's flexible multicanon. I understand why you did that but it doesn't jive with me.</p>
<p>That being said, this is a good, funny story if that version of Abel works for a given reader, especially if the reader knows much about sword-fighting (a lot of jargon was completely lost on me, which has less to do with your skill as an author and more to do with my own ignorance). This definitely has a place on the site, at least.</p>

							</div>

								
					
