														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-3796536">
									

<p>While I can definitely see some of that, I feel like the references to anime and the lines about katanas in particular really sold this version of Abel as a parody of the kind of people who idolize bladed weapons without understanding them. I would expect a real immortal demigod and avatar of war to at least know how much he doesn't know.</p>
<p>Another take on this is, he's never had a real challenger so he just assumed he was awesome at what he does. While funny in this context, I'm still not a huge fan.</p>
<p>As an aside, now I really want to read a story where someone like De Luca teaches Abel modern swordsmanship or possibly even firearms usage. &quot;Finger away from the trigger until you're ready to shoot. Now line up the sights and squeeeeze&#8230;&quot; *click* &quot;We just went over this! You need to charge the handle when you load a new magazine. It's not gonna magically reload itself!&quot; &quot;sorry&#8230;&quot;</p>

							</div>

								
					
